thread.title: Godfreys enjoys profit lift

title: Godfreys enjoys profit lift
text:
Thu, Aug 20, 2015, 9:42 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 18 mins. Godfreys enjoys profit lift Print 
Vacuum cleaner retailer Godfreys has lifted its full year profit by a third and is paying a special dividend to shareholders. 
The retailer's underlying net profit rose 33.7 per cent to $11.49 million in the year to June 30 from $8.6 million in 2013/14, while revenue rose 5.2 per cent to $182.6 million. 
Godfreys, which listed on the Australian share market in December 2014, announced a partly franked final dividend of 12.8 cents a share plus a special 2.6 cent dividend. 
Its statutory net profit, which includes the cost of its share market listing plus various accounting changes and one-benefits, more than doubled to $12 million from $5.7 million. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook AMP half-year profit up 33% AAP
